title: Watch: Portland Timbers 4, Colorado Rapids 1 highlights
text:
The Portland Timbers defeated the Colorado Rapids 4-1 on Sunday at Providence Park in the final regular-season game for both teams.
For the Portland, the win clinched the No. 3 spot in Major League Soccer's Western Conference and the Timbers will take on Sporting Kansas City on Thursday at Providence Park in the one-game knockout round. Colorado, which came into the game in last place, ends its season with the loss.
The Timbers were led by Darlington Nagbe , the dynamic midfielder who scored two goals in the first half.
